-- A `=>`-constrained helper crossing the module boundary — the case E6
-- (threading `=>`-constrained-function dict params on the `elaborateModules`
-- emit path) unlocks.  `Ord2` + its `Int` impl + the constrained helper
-- `clampU : Ord2 a => a -> a -> a -> a` all live HERE (methods do not yet
-- resolve cross-module through the selfhost typed pipeline); the ENTRY imports
-- `clampU` and applies it at the concrete `Int` type.
--
-- `clampU`'s body dispatches `lt2`/`gt2` on the constraint variable `a`.  Under
-- dict-passing it takes a leading `$dict_clampU_0` PARAM and routes those inner
-- method calls RDict through it.  Pre-E6 the multi-module emit path called
-- `dictPass []` (empty dict-name set), so `clampU` got NO leading param and the
-- emitter reported its body witness `$dict_clampU_0` UNBOUND (census-B reason
-- #11, "unbound dict witness").  E6 computes the proper prelude+module dict-name
-- set and dict-passes `clampU`, so the param is bound and the witness resolves.
export interface Ord2 a where
  lt2 : a -> a -> Bool
  gt2 : a -> a -> Bool

export impl Ord2 Int where
  lt2 a b = a < b
  gt2 a b = a > b

-- Ord2 a => : the constrained signature that must be dict-passed.  Bodied as a
-- nested if so both `lt2` and `gt2` (the constraint-variable method calls that
-- read the threaded dict) fire.
export
clampU : Ord2 a => a -> a -> a -> a
clampU lo hi x =
  if lt2 x lo then lo
  else if gt2 x hi then hi
  else x
